CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1962, pg. 11 reads: "Admiring African Violet - Mrs. Cornelia Brooks, right, admires the beautiful African Violet plant which her daughter, Mrs. Jayne McDaniel is holding. Mrs. Brooks who has a hand with flowers, assists with the care of the many lovely plants, similar to the window display here, that can be found all over the McDaniel home on Oberlin St.  Mrs. McDaniel is a member of the Knitty Pine Garden Club. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Jayne McDaniel holding African Violet flower and Cornelia Brooks, standing in front of window with plants
